11/02/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Friday (February 9th), four months after the legislative elections, BiH state parliament approved the new government of the country, led by Bosnian Serb politician Nikola Spiric. Spiric vowed his administration would work for Euro-Atlantic integration, with police reform as its first task. He also urged the media to provide co-operation and support. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 10/02/07; RTRS, Fena, PBS, BBC - 09/02/07)
